1.title: Episode #1.1

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: Steve and Paul attend the eviction of an army veteran whose debts have resulted in the repossession of his house. Meantime, Terry and Mike head to Liverpool to seize a car from a debtor who has refused to pay his bill.

2.title: Episode #1.2

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: Mike and Terry travel to Cheshire to seize a vehicle from a woman who owes several hundred pounds on a loan. Later, they head to Liverpool to recover a vehicle which the owner has failed to keep up the repayments for.

3.title: Episode #1.3

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Steve Wood has to repossess a classic corner shop. Meanwhile, Steve and Paul are tasked to evict a vulnerable pair of hoarders, and also find that a writ to seize a taxi has been made out to the wrong man.

4.title: Episode #1.4

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: Paul and Steve evict two groups of tenants from a house which the landlord is looking to renovate. Later they attend an eviction of a house with poor living conditions, but have a decision to make when the eviction runs into nightfall, and attend a flat eviction in an expensive area of London.

5.title: Final Demand

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: Paul and Steve attend an eviction where the tenant owes more than £26,000 in rent on his country estate residence. Later, they deal with a family of sitting tenants in a £5 million house.

1.title: Episode #2.1

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: Paul and Steve attend an eviction where a young mother of two is being evicted from her flat. Brian and Graham attend an eviction in South London where trouble is expected the eviction goes smoothly until they find a cannabis factory.

2.title: Episode #2.2

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: Steve and Paul deal with the unpaid debt of former professional footballer Neil Ruddock. Iain and Stewart attempt to reclaim a debt owed by a builder, but are threatened with violence by the man and his friends from the building site.

3.title: Episode #2.3

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Stewart and Iain find themselves in a spot of bother when some angry locals threaten a riot over an unpaid debt at a Liverpool computer shop. Paul and Steve evict a young woman with two children.

4.title: Episode #2.4

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: Paul and Steve evict a young mum and her two children for non-payment of rent. Brian and Graham repossess a car owned by a man who owes more than £3,000 to a telephone communications company.

5.title: Episode #2.5

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: Paul and Steve evict a family for non-payment of rent, but discover a dispute with the letting agent has led to the eviction. Stuart and Iain are faced with threats when they try to reclaim a debt of over £3,000.

6.title: Episode #2.6

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

6.plot: Steve and Ben attempt to evict a gang of squatters taking up residence in a central London office block. Later, they head to the home of a heavily pregnant tenant and her family, whom they are forced to evict due to non-payment of rent.

7.title: Episode #2.7

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

7.plot: Brian and Graham find themselves in a spot of bother at Swindon Town Football Club as they try to reclaim money on an unpaid debt. Paul and Steve make an interesting discovery during an eviction at a flat where they find $8.5 million.

8.title: Episode #2.8

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

8.plot: Brian and Graham arrive at a restaurant in north London to collect unpaid rent, they later attend a Korean education school to collect unpaid rent. Paul and Ben are called in to evict squatters from a residential property.

9.title: Episode #2.9

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

9.plot: Brian and Graham head to a Brighton health spa to speak to seize assets against the debt of £20,000, they also head to South London to find a man who owes £1,600 and to Dunsfold to reclaim money owed to a telephone answering service.

10.title: Eviction Special

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

10.plot: Steve and Paul attend the eviction of a multi-occupancy house and attend an eviction with a twist when they discover that the landlord trying to reclaim the property is the debtor's mother.

3.title: Can't Pay We'll Take It Away

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Kevin joins Brian to attend a Turkish restaurant to reclaim £4,500 owed to a company. Paul and Steve are called to an eviction where the landlord wants to move back into his property. Brian and Dael call on a man owing more than £16,000.

6.title: Episode #3.6

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

6.plot: Paul and Steve deal with a single mother being evicted by her landlady after amassing more than £11,000 in rent arrears. Stuart and Elmor deal with a tricky debtor who owes more than £1,000.

2.title: Episode #4.2

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: Paul joins Steve to chase down a £30,000 debt owed by the Lotus F1 racing team to one of their former suppliers. Stewart and Elmor attempt to recover a debt of £2,700 owed by the owner of a garage.

8.title: Can't Pay Special: Big Family Bust Up

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

8.plot: Paul and Steve then attend an eviction, where the tenant has been behind on her rent for nearly six years. Brian and Del try to reclaim £38,000 owed by a cafe owner in unpaid rent. Paul and Steve evict a tenant who owes more than £8,000.

10.title: Episode #4.10

episode of.title: Can't Pay? We'll Take It Away! (TV Series 2014– )

10.plot: Brian and Del attempt to hunt down an elusive debtor, who has evaded capture before. Later they attempt to reclaim an £11,000 debt owed by a man and his partner for unpaid rent.
